info.ryankenney.jasync_driver

Interface SyncTask<A,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - The type of argument passed into this task. Use the Void type if you have no use for an argument.
    R - The type returned by the task. Use the Void type if you have no use for an argument.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Task<A,R>

    public interface SyncTask<A,R>
extends Task<A,R>
    Used to define a synchronous task managed by a JasyncDriver. At first it may not seem necessary to use SyncTask objects, since in contrast to asynchronous tasks, these need no special handling to operate synchronously. However, this is very misleading. See JasyncDriver for more information.
    Author:
    rkenney

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      R run(A arg)
      The method that executes the underlying synchronous action.

    • Method Detail

      • run

        R run(A arg)
        The method that executes the underlying synchronous action.
        Parameters:
        arg - Any argument passed into the task. Arguments are controlled by the DriverBody.run() definition(s) in which instances of this class is used.
        Returns:
        Any value resulting from the task. Simply null if the return type is Void.
